Mutual Fund Services | The Gemini Companies


































































Mutual Fund Services








Gemini partners with independent advisors to provide comprehensive, pooled investment solutions, such as open-end mutual funds, closed-end interval funds, closed-end funds, collective investment trusts (CIT), variable insurance trusts (VIT), exchange traded funds (ETFs), and Section 529 funds. We service these products in their own trusts or through one of ours – the Northern Lights Fund Trusts (NLFT), Two Roads Shared Trust, and Northern Lights Variable Trust (NLVT). All mutual funds are registered with the SEC in a trust format. Advisors can choose to launch their funds in either a shared, series, or standalone trust.










 







Getting Started: Mutual Funds & ETFs


Structures, FAQs, how to get started, and distribution challenges of mutual funds, insurance platform funds, and ETFs.





Why Advisors Start Mutual Funds


Starting a mutual fund offers many advantages, such as new business opportunities, increased operational efficiencies, and reduced transaction costs.

 






